# Cloudflare Pages redirects.
#
# 1. non-www → www 301. Google penalizes duplicate content,
#    so we canonicalize to https://www.antena.com.ar.
# 2. /api/img/* → worker. The Pages site is static
#    (no Astro adapter), so the image-resize proxy
#    lives on the API worker. We 302 (not 301) so
#    future moves don't poison the cache.
# 3. Trailing-slash policy: Pages adds a trailing slash by
#    default. We strip it for SEO consistency (the sitemap
#    and canonical URLs use no trailing slash).
# 4. /noticia/<id>/ → /noticia/<id> (same).
# 5. /api/* and /functions/* are handled by the worker
#    or Pages Functions; do NOT redirect those (other than
#    the explicit /api/img/* → worker rule above).

# ── non-www → www ──────────────────────────────────────────
https://antena.com.ar/* https://www.antena.com.ar/:splat 301!
http://antena.com.ar/*  https://www.antena.com.ar/:splat 301!

# ── Force HTTPS (defense-in-depth — Pages already does it,
#    but explicit is better for edge cases) ────────────────
http://www.antena.com.ar/* https://www.antena.com.ar/:splat 301!

# ── Image proxy ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Frontend points directly at the API worker
# (https://akira-api.miclusty.workers.dev/api/img?url=…)
# using full URLs in the components. The worker has
# CORS configured to allow https://www.antena.com.ar.
